ieee8021AsTimeSyncMib.description: The Management Information Base module for IEEE 802.1AS time synchronization protocol.

ClockIdentity.name: ClockIdentity
ClockIdentity.description: Represents an 802 MAC address represented in the `canonical' order defined by IEEE 802.1a, EUI-64. EUI-48 converts to EUI-64 as specified by IEEE. The convertion assigns values 255 and 254 to octets 3 and 4 respectively, where octet 0 is the most significant and octet 7 the least. For example, EUI-48 of AC:DE:48:23:45:67 would extend to AC:DE:48:FF:FE:23:45:67.

IEEE8021ASClockClassValue.name: IEEE8021ASClockClassValue
IEEE8021ASClockClassValue.description: Clock Class Value from IEEE Std 1588-2008 7.6.2.4, with the following interpretation placed on the value: 6: A clock that is synchronized to a primary refernce time source, 7: A clock that has previously been designated as clockClass 6 but that has lost the ability to synchronize to a primary reference time source and is in holdover mode and within holdover specifications, 13: A clock that is synchronized to an application-specific source of time, 14: A clock that has previously been designated as clockClass 13 but that has lost the ability to synchronize to an application-specific source of time and is in holdover mode and within holdover specifications, 52: Degradation alternative A for a clock of clockClass 7 that is not within holdover specification, 58: Degradation alternative A for a clock of clockClass 14 that is not within holdover specification, 68..122: For use by alternate PTP profiles (68..122), 133..170: For use by alternate PTP profiles (133..170), 187: Degradation alternative B for a clock of clockClass 7 that is not within holdover specification, 193: Degradation alternative B for a clock of clockClass 14 that is not within holdover specification, 216..232: For use by alternate PTP profiles, 248: Default none of the other clockClass definitions apply, 255: A slave-only clock(255).

IEEE8021ASClockAccuracyValue.name: IEEE8021ASClockAccuracyValue
IEEE8021ASClockAccuracyValue.description: Clock Accuracy Value from 8.6.2.3, with the following interpretation placed on the value: 32: The time is accurate to within 25 ns, 33: The time is accurate to within 100 ns, 34: The time is accurate to within 250 ns, 35: The time is accurate to within 1 us, 36: The time is accurate to within 2.5 us, 37: The time is accurate to within 10 us, 38: The time is accurate to within 25 us, 39: The time is accurate to within 100 us, 40: The time is accurate to within 250 us, 41: The time is accurate to within 1 ms, 42: The time is accurate to within 2.5 ms, 43: The time is accurate to within 10 ms, 44: The time is accurate to within 25 ms, 45: The time is accurate to within 100 ms, 46: The time is accurate to within 250 ms, 47: The time is accurate to within 1 s, 48: The time is accurate to within 10 s, 49: The time is accurate to within > 10 s, 254: Default indicating unknown

IEEE8021ASTimeSourceValue.name: IEEE8021ASTimeSourceValue
IEEE8021ASTimeSourceValue.description: The timeSource is an information only attribute indicating the type of source of time used by a ClockMaster, representing categories. For example, the GPS entry would include not only the GPS system of the U.S. Department of Defense but the European Galileo system and other present and future satellite-based timing systems. In the absence of a default value set by a user of this standard, the default value of timeSource shall be OTHER. See 7.6.2.6 of IEEE Std 1588 - 2008 for more detailed description of timeSourceIndicates the source of time used by the grandmaster clock. The following interpretation placed on the value: 16: Atomic Clock, 32: GPS, 48: Terrestrial Radio, 64: PTP, 80: NTP, 96: Hand Set, 144: Other, 160: Internal Oscillator

ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockIdentity.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockIdentity
ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockIdentity.description: Globally unique manufacturer-assigned clock identifier for the local clock. The identifier is based on an EUI-64.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSNumberPorts.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSNumberPorts
ieee8021AsDefaultDSNumberPorts.description: The number of PTP ports on the device. Ordinary clocks have a single port.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockClass.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockClass
ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockClass.description: Denotes the traceability of the time or frequency of the local clock.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockAccuracy.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockAccuracy
ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockAccuracy.description: Characterizes local clock for the purpose of the best master clock algorithm.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSOffsetScaledLogVarian.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSOffsetScaledLogVariance
ieee8021AsDefaultDSOffsetScaledLogVarian.description: Clock variance of the local clock expressed as a base-2 logarithm multiplied by a scale factor of 256. Hysteresis is applied requiring the underlying computed variance to move by at least 128 before a change is reported. A value of -37268 indicates value is too large to be represented or has not been computed.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSPriority1.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSPriority1
ieee8021AsDefaultDSPriority1.description: Most-significant priority declaration in the execution of the best master clock algorithm. Lower values take precedence. The value of priority1 shall be 255 for a time-aware system that is not grandmaster-capable. The value of priority1 shall be less than 255 for a time-aware system that is grandmaster-capable. The value 0 shall be reserved for future management use, i.e., the valueof priority1 shall be set to 0 only via management action, and shall not be specified as a default value by a user of this standard.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSPriority2.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSPriority2
ieee8021AsDefaultDSPriority2.description: Least-significant priority declaration in the execution of the best master clock algorithm. Lower values take precedence. The default value is 248

ieee8021AsDefaultDSGmCapable.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSGmCapable
ieee8021AsDefaultDSGmCapable.description: True (1) if master clock capable; false (2) otherwise.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSCurrentUTCOffset.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSCurrentUTCOffset
ieee8021AsDefaultDSCurrentUTCOffset.description: The value of defaultDScurrentUTCOffset is the offset in seconds between TAI and UTC.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSCurrentUTCOffsetValid.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSCurrentUTCOffsetValid
ieee8021AsDefaultDSCurrentUTCOffsetValid.description: True (1) if defaultDSCurrentUTCOffset is known to be correct; false (2) otherwise.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap59.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap59
ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap59.description: In PTP systems whose epoch is the PTP epoch, a true (1) value indicates that the last minute of the current UTC day contains 59 seconds. If the epoch is not PTP, or the last minute of the UTC day contains 60 seconds, the value is false (2).

ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap61.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap61
ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap61.description: In PTP systems whose epoch is the PTP epoch, a true (1) value indicates that the last minute of the current UTC day contains 61 seconds. If the epoch is not PTP, or the last minute of the UTC day contains 60 seconds, the value is false (2).

ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeTraceable.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeTraceable
ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeTraceable.description: True (1) if the timescale and the value of defaultDSCurrentUTCOffset are traceable to a primary reference; false (2) otherwise.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSFrequencyTraceable.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSFrequencyTraceable
ieee8021AsDefaultDSFrequencyTraceable.description: True (1) if the frequency determining the timescale is traceable to a primary reference; false (2) otherwise.

ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeSource.name: ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeSource
ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeSource.description: Indicates the source of time used by the grandmaster clock.

ieee8021AsCurrentDSStepsRemoved.name: ieee8021AsCurrentDSStepsRemoved
ieee8021AsCurrentDSStepsRemoved.description: The number of communication paths traversed between the local clock and the grandmaster clock. For example, 2 switch from GM, then the value is 3.

ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterHs.name: ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterHs
ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterHs.description: The most significant 32 bits of the offset, signed 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, an implementation-specific computation of the current value of the time difference between a master and a slave as computed by the slave. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterMs, and ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterLs, which represents middle and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed.

ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterMs.name: ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterMs
ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterMs.description: The middle significant 32 bits of the offset, signed 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, an implementation-specific computation of the current value of the time difference between a master and a slave as computed by the slave. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterHs, and ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterLs, which represents most (highest) and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed.

ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterLs.name: ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterLs
ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterLs.description: The least significant 32 bits of the offset, signed 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, an implementation-specific computation of the current value of the time difference between a master and a slave as computed by the slave. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterHs, and ieee8021AsCurrentDSOffsetFromMasterMs, which represents most (highest) and middle significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed.

ieee8021AsParentDSParentClockIdentity.name: ieee8021AsParentDSParentClockIdentity
ieee8021AsParentDSParentClockIdentity.description: Clock identifier (clockIdentity) of the local clock's parent clock. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockIdentity.

ieee8021AsParentDSParentPortNumber.name: ieee8021AsParentDSParentPortNumber
ieee8021AsParentDSParentPortNumber.description: Port number (portNumber)of the local clock.s parent clock. The initial value is zero.

ieee8021AsParentDSCumlativeRateRatio.name: ieee8021AsParentDSCumlativeRateRatio
ieee8021AsParentDSCumlativeRateRatio.description: An estimate of the ratio of the frequency of the grandmaster to the frequency of the LocalClock entity of this time-aware system. Cumulative rate ratio is expressed as the fractional frequency offset multiplied by 2**41, i.e., the quantity (rateRatio - 1.0)(2**41), where rateRatio is computed by the PortSyncSyncReceive state machine (see 10.2.7.1.4).

ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterIdentity.name: ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterIdentity
ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterIdentity.description: Clock identifier (clockIdentity) of the grandmaster. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockIdentity.

ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterClockClass.name: ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterClockClass
ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterClockClass.description: Denotes the traceability of the time or frequency of the grandmaster. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockClass.

ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterClockAccura.name: ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterClockAccuracy
ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterClockAccura.description: Characterizes the grandmaster clock for the purpose of the best master clock algorithm. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSClockAccuracy.

ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterOffsetScale.name: ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterOffsetScaledLogVariance
ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterOffsetScale.description: Clock Allan variance of the local clock expressed as a base-2 logarithm multiplied by a scale factor of 256. Hysteresis is applied requiring the underlying computed variance to move by at least 128 before a change is reported. A value of -37268 indicates value is too large to be represented or has not been computed. The initialvalue is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSOffsetScaledLogVariance.

ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterPriority1.name: ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterPriority1
ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterPriority1.description: Grandmaster's most-significant priority declaration in the execution of the best master clock algorithm. Lower values take precedence. The initialvalue is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSPriority1.

ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterPriority2.name: ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterPriority2
ieee8021AsParentDSGrandmasterPriority2.description: Grandmaster's least-significant priority declaration in the execution of the best master clock algorithm. Lower values take precedence. The initialvalue is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSDSPriority2.

ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSCurrentUtcOffs.name: ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSCurrentUtcOffset
ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSCurrentUtcOffs.description: The value of timePropertiesDScurrentUTCOffset is the offset in seconds between TAI and UTC.

ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSCurrentUtcOffs.name: ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSCurrentUtcOffsetValid
ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSCurrentUtcOffs.description: True (1) if timePropertiesDSCurrentUTCOffset is known to be correct; false (2) otherwise. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSCurrentUTCOffsetValid.

ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSLeap59.name: ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSLeap59
ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSLeap59.description: In PTP systems whose epoch is the PTP epoch, a true (1) value indicates that the last minute of the current UTC day contains 59 seconds. If the epoch is not PTP, or the last minute of the UTC day contains 60 seconds, the value is false (2). The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap59.

ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSLeap61.name: ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSLeap61
ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSLeap61.description: In PTP systems whose epoch is the PTP epoch, a true (1) value indicates that the last minute of the current UTC day contains 61 seconds. If the epoch is not PTP, or the last minute of the UTC day contains 60 seconds, the value is false (2). The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSLeap61.

ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSTimeTraceable.name: ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSTimeTraceable
ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSTimeTraceable.description: True (1) if the timescale and the value of timePropertiesDSCurrentUTCOffset are traceable to a primary reference; false (2) otherwise. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeTraceable.

ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSFrequencyTrace.name: ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSFrequencyTraceable
ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSFrequencyTrace.description: True (1) if the frequency determining the timescale is traceable to a primary reference; false (2) otherwise. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSFrequencyTraceable.

ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSTimeSource.name: ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSTimeSource
ieee8021AsTimePropertiesDSTimeSource.description: Indicates the source of time used by the grandmaster clock. The initial value is set to ieee8021AsDefaultDSTimeSource.

ieee8021AsPortDSIfTable.name: ieee8021AsPortDSIfTable
ieee8021AsPortDSIfTable.description: A table of time-aware port related variables in a time-aware bridge or for a time-aware end station. A value of 1 is used in a bridge or an end station that does not have multiple components.

ieee8021AsPortDSIfEntry.name: ieee8021AsPortDSIfEntry
ieee8021AsPortDSIfEntry.description: A list of objects pertaining to a port of a time-aware bridge component or a time-aware end station.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSClockIdentity.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSClockIdentity
ifIeee8021AsPortDSClockIdentity.description: Globally unique manufacturer-assigned clock identifier for the local clock port. The identifier is based on an EUI-64.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSPortRole.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSPortRole
ifIeee8021AsPortDSPortRole.description: The value is the value of the port role of this port (see Table 10-1), and is taken from the enumeration in Table 14-5. All other values reserved. The enumeration values are consistent with IEEE Std 1588TM-2008, Table 8. The initialization value is 3 (DisabledPort).

ifIeee8021AsPortDSPttPortEnabled.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSPttPortEnabled
ifIeee8021AsPortDSPttPortEnabled.description: 802.1AS function enable for a given port. True (1) if the time-synchronization and best master selection functions of the port are enabled; False (2) otherwise. The contents of this table SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSIsMeasuringPdelay.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSIsMeasuringPdelay
ifIeee8021AsPortDSIsMeasuringPdelay.description: True (1) if the port is measuring link propagation delay; False (2) otherwise.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSAsCapable.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSAsCapable
ifIeee8021AsPortDSAsCapable.description: True (1) if and only if it is determined that this time-aware ystem and the time-aware system at the other ends of the link attached to this port can interoperate with each other via the IEEE 802.1AS protocol; False (2) otherwise.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayHs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayHs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayHs.description: The most (highest) significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, the value is equal to the value of the per-port global variable neighborPropDelay (see 10.2.4.6). It is an estimate of the current one-way propagation time on the link attached to this port, measured as specified for the respective medium (see 11.2.15, 12.5, and E.4). The value is zero for ports attached to IEEE 802.3 EPON links and for the master port of an IEEE 802.11 link, because one-way propagation delay is not measured on the latter and not directly measured on the former. It is recommended that the data type be scaled in ns. The initialization value is zero. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayMs, and ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayLs, which represents middle and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayMs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayMs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayMs.description: The second most (middle) significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, the value is equal to the value of the per-port global variable neighborPropDelay (see 10.2.4.6). It is an estimate of the current one-way propagation time on the link attached to this port, measured as specified for the respective medium (see 11.2.15, 12.5, and E.4). The value is zero for ports attached to IEEE 802.3 EPON links and for the master port of an IEEE 802.11 link, because one-way propagation delay is not measured on the latter and not directly measured on the former. It is recommended that the data type be scaled in ns. The initialization value is zero. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayLs, which represents most (highest) and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayLs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayLs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayLs.description: The least significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, the value is equal to the value of the per-port global variable neighborPropDelay (see 10.2.4.6). It is an estimate of the current one-way propagation time on the link attached to this port, measured as specified for the respective medium (see 11.2.15, 12.5, and E.4). The value is zero for ports attached to IEEE 802.3 EPON links and for the master port of an IEEE 802.11 link, because one-way propagation delay is not measured on the latter and not directly measured on the former. It is recommended that the data type be scaled in ns. The initialization value is zero. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayMs, which represents most (highest) and middle significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThres.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshHs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThres.description: The most (highest) significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, the value is equal to the value of the per-port global variable neighborPropDelayThresh (see 11.2.12.5). It is the propagation time threshold, above which a port is not considered capable of participating in the 802.1AS protocol This object MUST be read or writen at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshMs, and ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshLs, which represents middle and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThres.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshMs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThres.description: The middle significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, the value is equal to the value of the per-port global variable neighborPropDelayThresh (see 11.2.12.5). It is the propagation time threshold, above which a port is not considered capable of participating in the 802.1AS protocol This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshLs, which represents most (highest) and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThres.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshLs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThres.description: The least significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns, the value is equal to the value of the per-port global variable neighborPropDelayThresh (see 11.2.12.5). It is the propagation time threshold, above which a port is not considered capable of participating in the 802.1AS protocol This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSNeighborPropDelayThreshMs, which represents most (highest) and middle significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryHs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryHs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryHs.description: The most (highest) significant 32 bits, signed 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns. For ports attached to full-duplex, IEEE 802.3 media, the value is the propagation delay asymmetry (see 8.3), which is equal to the per-port global variable delayAsymmetry (see 10.2.4.7). The initialization value is the propagation delay asymmetry between transmit and receive in the physical layer path, if known, or 0 otherwise. For ports attached to other media, the value is 0. This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryMs, and ieee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryLs, which represents middle and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryMs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryMs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryMs.description: The middle significant 32 bits, signed 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns. For ports attached to full-duplex, IEEE 802.3 media, the value is the propagation delay asymmetry (see 8.3), which is equal to the per-port global variable delayAsymmetry (see 10.2.4.7). The initialization value is the propagation delay asymmetry between transmit and receive in the physical layer path, if known, or 0 otherwise. For ports attached to other media, the value is 0. This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryLs, which represents middle and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryLs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryLs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryLs.description: The least significant 32 bits, signed 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns. For ports attached to full-duplex, IEEE 802.3 media, the value is the propagation delay asymmetry (see 8.3), which is equal to the per-port global variable delayAsymmetry (see 10.2.4.7). The initialization value is the propagation delay asymmetry between transmit and receive in the physical layer path, if known, or 0 otherwise. For ports attached to other media, the value is 0. This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSDelayAsymmetryLs, which represents most (highest) and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborRateRatio.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborRateRatio
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNeighborRateRatio.description: An estimate of the ratio of the frequency of the LocalClock entity of the time-aware system at the other end of the link attached to this port, to the frequency of the LocalClock entity of this time-aware system (see 10.2.4.5). Neighbor rate ratio is expressed as the fractional frequency offset multiplied by 2**41, i.e., the quantity (neighborRateRatio - 1.0)(2**41).

ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogAnnounceInterval.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogAnnounceInterval
ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogAnnounceInterval.description: The value is the logarithm to the base 2 of the of the Announce message transmission interval, see 10.6.2.2. The initialization value is 0. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSAnnounceReceiptTimeout.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSAnnounceReceiptTimeout
ifIeee8021AsPortDSAnnounceReceiptTimeout.description: The value is the number of Announce message transmission intervals that a slave port waits without receiving an Announce message, before assuming that the master is no longer transmitting Announce messages and the BMCA needs to be run, if appropriate. The initialization value is 2. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogSyncInterval.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogSyncInterval
ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogSyncInterval.description: The value is the logarithm to the base 2 of the time-synchronization transmission interval, see 10.6.2.3. The initialization value is -3. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeout.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeout
ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeout.description: The value is the number of time-synchronization transmission inervals that a slave port waits without receiving synchronization information, before assuming that the master is no longer transmitting synchronization information and that the BMCA needs to be run, if appropriate. The initialziation value is 3. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTime.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalHs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTime.description: The most (highest) significant 32 bits, of unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns. The value is equal to the value of the per port global variable syncReceiptTimeoutTimeInterval (see 10.2.4.2). It is the time interval after which sync receipt timeout occurs if time-synchronization information has not been received during the interval. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalMs, and ieee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalLs, which represents middle and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed. Default value is calculated per 10.2.4.2, or '0000 0000 0000 165A 0BC0 0000'h. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTime.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalMs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTime.description: The middle significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns. The value is equal to the value of the per port global variable syncReceiptTimeoutTimeInterval (see 10.2.4.2). It is the time interval after which sync receipt timeout occurs if time-synchronization information has not been received during the interval. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalLs, which represents most (highest) and least significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed. Default value is calculated per 10.2.4.2, or '0000 0000 0000 165A 0BC0 0000'h. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTime.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalLs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTime.description: The least significant 32 bits, unsigned 96 bit number in 2**-16 ns. The value is equal to the value of the per port global variable syncReceiptTimeoutTimeInterval (see 10.2.4.2). It is the time interval after which sync receipt timeout occurs if time-synchronization information has not been received during the interval. This object MUST be read at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalHs, and ieee8021AsPortDSSyncReceiptTimeoutTimeIntervalMs, which represents most (highest) and middle significant 32 bits of values, respectively, in order for the read operation to succeed. Default value is calculated per 10.2.4.2, or '0000 0000 0000 165A 0BC0 0000'h. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogPdelayReqInterval.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogPdelayReqInterval
ifIeee8021AsPortDSLogPdelayReqInterval.description: For full-duplex, IEEE 802.3 media and CSN media that use the peer delay mechanism to measure path delay (see E.4.3.1), the value is the logarithm to the base 2 of the Pdelay_Req message transmission interval, see 11.5.2.2. For these media, the initialization value is 0. For all other media, the value is 127. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSAllowedLostResponses.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSAllowedLostResponses
ifIeee8021AsPortDSAllowedLostResponses.description: The value is equal to the value of the per-port global variable allowedLostResponses (see 11.2.12.3). It is the number of Pdelay_Req messages for which a valid response is not received, above which a port is considered to not be exchanging peer delay messages with its neighbor. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSVersionNumber.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSVersionNumber
ifIeee8021AsPortDSVersionNumber.description: Indicates the PTP version in use on the port. The version number for this standard is set to the value 2. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNupMs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNupMs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNupMs.description: The most significant 32 bits, of unsigned 64 bit fixed point number between 0 and less than 2. For an OLT port of an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the value is the effective index of refraction for the EPON upstream wavelength light of the optical path (see 13.1.4 and 13.7.1.2). The initialization value is 1. For all other ports, the value is 0. This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNupLs, which represents least significant 32 bits of the value in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNupLs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNupLs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNupLs.description: The least significant 32 bits, of unsigned 64 bit fixed point number between 0 and less than 2. For an OLT port of an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the value is the effective index of refraction for the EPON upstream wavelength light of the optical path (see 13.1.4 and 13.7.1.2). The initialization value is 1. For all other ports, the value is 0. This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNupMs, which represents the most significant 32 bits of the value in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNdownMs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNdownMs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNdownMs.description: The least significant 32 bits, of unsigned 64 bit fixed point number between 0 and less than 2. For an OLT port of an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the value is the effective index of refraction for the EPON downstream wavelength light of the optical path (see 13.1.4 and 13.7.1.2). The initialization value is 1.0. other ports, the value is 0. This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNdownLs, which represents the least significant 32 bits of the value in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSNdownLs.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSNdownLs
ifIeee8021AsPortDSNdownLs.description: The least significant 32 bits, of unsigned 64 bit fixed point number between 0 and less than 2. For an OLT port of an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the value is the effective index of refraction for the EPON downstream wavelength light of the optical path (see 13.1.4 and 13.7.1.2). The initialization value is 1.0. other ports, the value is 0. This object MUST be read or written at the same time as ieee8021AsPortDSNdownMs, which represents the most significant 32 bits of the value in order for the read or write operation to succeed. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ifIeee8021AsPortDSAcceptableMasterTableE.name: ifIeee8021AsPortDSAcceptableMasterTableEnabled
ifIeee8021AsPortDSAcceptableMasterTableE.description: True (1) if acceptableMasterTableEnabled (see 13.1.3) in a time-aware system contains an ONU port attached to an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the default value is TRUE; False (2) if the time-aware system does not contain an ONU port attached to an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the default value is FALSE. The contents of this variable SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMaxTabl.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMaxTableSize
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMaxTabl.description: The value is the maximum size of the AcceptableMasterTable. It is equal to the maxTableSize member of the AcceptableMasterTable structure (see 13.1.3.2)

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSActualT.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSActualTableSize
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSActualT.description: The value is the actual size of the AcceptableMasterTable. It is equal to the actualTableSize member of the AcceptableMasterTable structure (see 13.1.3.2), i.e., the current number of elements in the acceptable master array. The actual table size is less than or equal to the max table size. This value SHOULD be reflect the number of entries in the ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterTable. For a time-aware system that contains an ONU attached to an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the initialization value is 1. For a time-aware system that does not contain an ONU attached to an IEEE 802.3 EPON link, the initialization value is 0.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterT.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterTable
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterT.description: A table of time-aware port related variables in a time-aware bridge or for a time-aware end station. A value of 1 is used in a bridge or an end station that does not have multiple components. The contents of this table SHALL be maintained across a restart of the system.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterE.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterEntry
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterE.description: A list of objects pertaining to a port of a time-aware bridge component or a time-aware end station.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterI.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterId
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableDSMasterI.description: Acceptbale Master row entry index in this ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTabdDSMaster Entry applies. If the does not contain Media type of EPON, this variable (index) MUST be equalto 0.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterClockIdentity.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterClockIdentity
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterClockIdentity.description: Globally unique manufacturer-assigned clock identifier for the local clock port. The identifier is based on an EUI-64.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterPortNumber.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterPortNumber
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterPortNumber.description: This object represents a Port or aggregated port on a bridge component or end-station. This object and ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterClockIdentity together forms AccetpableMasterDS Port Identity.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterAlternatePrior.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterAlternatePriority1
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterAlternatePrior.description: If the alternatePriority1 member of the AcceptableMaster array element that corresponds to the sourcePortIdentity of a received Announce message is greater than 0, the value of the grandmasterPriority1 field of the Announce message is replaced by the value of alternatePriority1 of this AcceptableMaster array element for use in the invocation of BMCA

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterRowStatus.name: ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterRowStatus
ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of an entry, and is used to create/delete entries.

ieee8021ASSystemDefaultReqdGroup.name: ieee8021ASSystemDefaultReqdGroup
ieee8021ASSystemDefaultReqdGroup.description: Objects in the System Default required global group.

ieee8021ASSystemCurrentGroup.name: ieee8021ASSystemCurrentGroup
ieee8021ASSystemCurrentGroup.description: Objects in the System Current global group.

ieee8021AsSystemClockParentGroup.name: ieee8021AsSystemClockParentGroup
ieee8021AsSystemClockParentGroup.description: Objects in the Clock Parent global group.

ieee8021AsSystemTimePropertiesGroup.description: Objects for the Time Properties Global group.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterBaseGroup.description: Objects for the Acceptble Master group.

ieee8021AsAcceptableMasterTableGroup.description: Objects for the Acceptble Master group.
